The Kidrobot.com Exclusive KRAK 8" Dunny - Plasma Stone edition is available now at Kidrobot.com (while supplies last)!!! Limited edition of 400. "The Krak design was inspired by the Shard design which was originally a design that was going to be in The Odd Ones blind box series. With designing Krak I wanted to do something a little different than I what I usually do. Typically, I like to go pretty heavy on graphics, decals, etc. to support either a basic sculpt. My goal for this one was to have the sculpt be strong enough to not need any graphic assistance. Instead, the translucent material would support the sculpt. I like the way light can interact with faceted clear objects. So with this piece I think the lighting in which you display the piece is important. I'm excited to see this piece come to life and hope Kidrobot fans will enjoy it as well!" @MrScottTolleson

Drops at 10am MT - Following last years sold out 15th Anniversary New Money Metal Dunny release, Tristan Eaton returns to Kidrobot to create the second edition of the 5-inch New Money Metal Dunny with the Rose Gold Edition. Etched into rose gold colored metal and decorated in iconic Tristan Eaton style, this Dunny redefines the limits of the forever recognizable art platform created over 15 years ago. Transcending art from canvas to metal art toy sculpture, this Dunny stands as an honorary piece to the last 15 years the Dunny has given dedicated artists and collectors a creative platform. Limited to 1000 pieces worldwide. Available while supplies last at Kidrobot.com at art toy stores today at 10am MT.

The Dunny has EVOLVED letting you now interchange the parts with the power of magnets in the new Exquisite Corpse Dunny Series!  This series features the talented artists of Red Mutuca Studios with a corpse-tastic theme.  Collect and hunt down all 15 designs right now at Kidrobot.com and your favorite art toy retailer!

#ExquisiteCorpse #Dunny #ArtToys #Kidrobot #RedMutuca #collectible #vinyltoys #artists #art #artist #exquisitecorpsedunnyseries

Kidrobot is excited to introduce the new Exquisite Corpse Dunny Series, available now on Kidrobot.com and select art toy retailers.  The artists of Red Mutuca Studios have breathed new life into the Dunny platform, creating an otherworldly rendition that can split apart and be interchanged.

Have you ever dreamed of being Dr. Frankenstein, piecing together your own mad creation from various parts? Regardless of if you answered "yes" or "no", we're fairly certain that you'll love the Exquisite Corpse Dunny Series. Reimagining what the Dunny can be, this collection features a brand new version of the Dunny, one that is magnetically held together at the neck and waist, allowing you to easily interchange sections from the various designs!

Assembling the talented artists of Red Mutuca Studios, the Exquisite Corpse Dunny Series features designs by Chauskoskis, Gorgocho, Grimsheep, Igor Ventura, Luiz Unreal, MAp-MAp, Matucha, Mr. Mitote, Quiccs, RunDMB, Sergio Mancini, and Tim Munz. And while their designs look stellar straight out of the box, we're inviting you to mix and match the parts between these pieces to your heart's content. 
The Exquisite Corpse Dunny Series: Collect the Dunnys, become the artist.

REVEAL: JUNIOR G.O.K. by Philippines based artist Quiccs (2/24 Odds) from the upcoming Exquisite Corpse Dunny Series dropping tomorrow at 10am MT on Kidrobot.com and select retail stores. ‚ò†Ô∏è ‚ÄúThe Ghost of Kurosawa is one of our recurring characters in my Bulletpunk‚Ñ¢ Universe. It's a character in the post-apocalyptic future that has built his set of beliefs around pop culture materials from the past -- A combination of Akira Kurosawa's films, Japanese Anime shows, and popular science fiction movies. It's one of the earliest characters we developed together with TEQ63.

This design is my "thank you" to the guys who believed in my vision and style back when I was just starting in the designer toy scene. REVEAL: ANUBIS Dunny by Grimsheep (2/24 Odds) from the upcoming Exquisite Corpse Dunny Series.  Drops this Friday at 10am MT on Kidrobot.com and your favorite art toy stores! "As it happens, this design almost never came to be. I had my submissions ready to go but at the last minute was inspired to do one last one. Whereas the others were more literal in regards to the the theme, this one was a little different. I find Egyptian mythology fascinating, and while I knew Anubis was the god of death, it wasn't until I did a little research that I found he is also the god of embalming. Seeing as he is actually responsible for exquisite corpses, I thought he would be fitting. Plus, Egyptian gods look cool!" @grimsheep
